# Overstock.com
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** e-commerce / online retail  
**Website:** https://www.overstock.com

## Overview
Overstock.com is an online retailer that originally focused on liquidating excess inventory from manufacturers and distributors, offering deeply discounted branded merchandise across categories including furniture, home décor, electronics, and clothing. Founded in 1999 by Dr. Patrick M. Byrne, the company grew rapidly during the dot-com era and became one of the largest e-commerce platforms in the United States. Overstock was also an early adopter of Bitcoin as a payment method and later expanded into blockchain ventures via its subsidiary Medici Ventures, exploring applications in voting, supply chain, and real estate.

In 2023, Overstock.com acquired the intellectual property assets of Bed Bath & Beyond and rebranded its website as BedBathandBeyond.com; the corporate parent changed its name to Beyond Inc. Overstock’s legacy as an innovator in discount e-commerce and its early embrace of cryptocurrency helped shape the modern online retail landscape.

## Utah connection
Overstock.com is a flagship company of Utah’s “Silicon Slopes” technology cluster. Its headquarters have long been located in Midvale, Utah, a suburb of Salt Lake City. The company’s growth provided a key anchor for the region’s e‑commerce and tech ecosystem, attracting talent and investment to Utah. Overstock also funded and spun out several Utah-based blockchain and fintech startups through its Medici Ventures arm, further embedding itself in the state’s entrepreneurial fabric.

